'''步行'''，是有腿動物進行{{link-en|動物運動|Animal locomotion}}的主要{{link-en|步態|Gait}}之一，通常比[[跑步|跑步]]和其他步態慢。步行被定義為一種「[[倒單擺|倒單擺]]」的步態。在這種步態中，每走一步上身體都要拱起腳才能前進。步行不分肢的數量，即使是有超過一對足的[[節肢動物|節肢動物]]也可以步行。<ref> {{ cite journal |vauthors =Cavagna GA, Heglund NC, Taylor CR |year=1977 |title= Mechanical work in terrestrial locomotion: two basic mechanisms for minimizing energy expenditure. |journal=American Journal of Physiology |volume=233 |issue=5 |pages= R243-261|doi=10.1152/ajpregu.1977.233.5.R243}}</ref>人類的步行有時也定義為隨時保持一隻腳在地上的移動方式，若兩腳同時離地則稱為跑步或[[跳躍|跳躍]]。

==起源==
[[File:Gait-of-healthy-Hamster.ogv|thumb]]
根據理論，四足動物之間的“行走”源於水下。例如[[蝟鰩|蝟鰩]]（''Leucoraja erinacea''），是[[底層區|底層區]]魚類群落的一員，可以用它們的腹鰭以推離海底。早在4.2億年前，它們就進化出特有的神經機制以推動自己前進，這比脊椎動物踏上陸地要早<ref>H. Jung et al. [http://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(18)30050-3 The ancient origins of neural substrates for land walking.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(18)30050-3 |date=20190817212143 }} Cell. Vol. 172, 2018-02-08, p. 667. {{doi|10.1016/j.cell.2018.01.013}}</ref><ref>Garisto, Dan, [https://www.sciencenews.org/article/wiring-walking-developed-long-fish-left-sea?tgt=nr The wiring for walking developed long before fish left the sea] {{Wayback|url=https://www.sciencenews.org/article/wiring-walking-developed-long-fish-left-sea?tgt=nr |date=20201030222753 }} . {{link-en|Science News}} . 2018-02-08</ref>。呼吸空氣的魚類在水下用鰭“行走”，隨後產生像[[提塔利克魚屬|提塔利克魚屬]]這樣可以上陸的[[脊椎動物|脊椎動物]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Choi |first=Charles |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/45645209 |title=Hopping fish suggests walking originated underwater; Discovery might redraw the evolutionary route scientists think life took from water to land |publisher=NBC News |date=2011-12-12 |accessdate=2012-08-22 |archive-date=2020-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200910124626/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/45645209 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，之後再進化出生活在陸地上靠四肢行走的生物<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://evolution.berkeley.edu/evolibrary/news/060501_tiktaalik|title=What has the head of a crocodile and the gills of a fish?|website=evolution.berkeley.edu|access-date=2018-06-06|archive-date=2019-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424025847/https://evolution.berkeley.edu/evolibrary/news/060501_tiktaalik|dead-url=no}}</ref>。陸生四足動物理論上只有一個起源，四肢演化自魚鰭，而節肢動物和它們的近親，特別是在昆蟲、多足綱動物、螯蝦、緩步動物、甲狀旁腺動物和甲殼類動物，已被認為曾多次獨立進化了行走<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ql6Jl6wKb88C&pg=PA109&lpg=PA109&dq=arthropod+invasion+of+the+land#v=onepage |title=Evolution of the Insects – David Grimaldi, Michael S. Engel – Google Books |date=2005-05-16 |accessdate=2018-06-11 |isbn=9780521821490 |last1=Grimaldi |first1=David |last2=Engel |first2=Michael S. |last3=Engel |first3=Michael S. |archive-date=2020-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200910124636/https://books.google.com/books?id=Ql6Jl6wKb88C&pg=PA109&lpg=PA109&dq=arthropod+invasion+of+the+land#v=onepage |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

鳥類、大穿山甲、人類、以及一些肉食性恐龍獨立演化出{{le|二足步行|bipedalism}}，有些蜥蜴在高速跑步時也只用二足，[[袋鼠|袋鼠]]和[[跳鼠|跳鼠]]用二足跳躍移動。目前認為人類的二足步行始於約400萬年前的[[南猿|南猿]]。從[[肯尼亞|肯尼亞]]古海岸發現的腳印來看，人們認為在150萬年前現代人類的祖先很可能以與現在非常相似的方式行走<ref>{{cite news
